Hibernate provides various cascade types that dictate how operations on a parent entity affect the associated child entities.

1) CascadeType.ALL

Applies all cascading operations: PERSIST, MERGE, REMOVE, REFRESH, and DETACH.
Use when you want the child entity to completely follow the lifecycle of the parent.
CascadeType.PERSIST

2) CascadeType.PERSIST
Saves (persists) the child entity when the parent entity is persisted.
CascadeType.MERGE

3) CascadeType.MERGE
Updates the child entity when the parent entity is updated.

4) CascadeType.REMOVE
Deletes the child entity when the parent entity is deleted.
CascadeType.REFRESH

5) CascadeType.REFRESH
Updates the child entity's state to match the database when the parent entity is refreshed.
CascadeType.DETACH

6) CascadeType.DETACH
Detaches the child entity when the parent entity is detached from the persistence context.